{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CeXnLzNk7o8yuhKjy8k3Pa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 33 — state corruption fix #17, no-op (2026-03-27T15:44Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **State corruption fix #17**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, ralph stale process reverting statuses. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist.\n     6→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml.\n     7→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This is the 17th fix for this exact same issue.\n     8→\n     9→## Token Report\n    10→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    11→- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n    12→- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n    13→- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue\n    14→\n    15→### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)\n    16→\n    17→- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.\n    18→- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.\n    19→- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.\n    20→- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state.\n    21→\n    22→## Token Report\n    23→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    24→- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4\n    25→- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n    26→- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue\n    27→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"837dd5b1-3553-4ec3-8065-aeaf103da8eb","uuid":"e67e4b0c-3002-4417-a86b-4a9bd4850508","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:48:12.814Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 33 — state corruption fix #17, no-op (2026-03-27T15:44Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #17**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, ralph stale process reverting statuses. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist.\n- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml.\n- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This is the 17th fix for this exact same issue.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue\n\n### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.\n- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.\n- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.\n- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue\n","numLines":27,"startLine":1,"totalLines":27}}}
