{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017zn1matUPNVG1tZbpZ6wXF","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"837dd5b1-3553-4ec3-8065-aeaf103da8eb","uuid":"98dc7a2f-6c21-4d44-bb22-05c5ebf4b9a0","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:49:32.660Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 34 — state corruption fix #18, no-op (2026-03-27T15:48Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #18**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, epic-16 at `backlog`. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist in `verification/`.\n- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done` in sprint-status.yaml.\n- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This has been the same issue since session 31+. The fix deployed in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent ralph from reverting statuses of existing stories.\n- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 5, Glob: 1, Grep: 0\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":26,"newStart":1,"newLines":14,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27"," ","-### Session 33 — state corruption fix #17, no-op (2026-03-27T15:44Z)","+### Session 34 — state corruption fix #18, no-op (2026-03-27T15:48Z)"," ","-- **State corruption fix #17**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, ralph stale process reverting statuses. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist.","-- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml.","-- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This is the 17th fix for this exact same issue.","+- **State corruption fix #18**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, epic-16 at `backlog`. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist in `verification/`.","+- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done` in sprint-status.yaml.","+- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This has been the same issue since session 31+. The fix deployed in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent ralph from reverting statuses of existing stories.","+- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete."," "," ## Token Report"," - Total tool calls: ~12","-- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1","+- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 5, Glob: 1, Grep: 0"," - Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads"," - Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue","-","-### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)","-","-- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.","-- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.","-- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.","-- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state.","-","-## Token Report","-- Total tool calls: ~12","-- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4","-- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads","-- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue"]}],"originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 33 — state corruption fix #17, no-op (2026-03-27T15:44Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #17**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, ralph stale process reverting statuses. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist.\n- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml.\n- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This is the 17th fix for this exact same issue.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue\n\n### Session 32 — state corruption fix #16, no-op (2026-03-27T15:39Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #16**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, phantom `1-1-foo` present. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits exist with \"verified and done\" messages) and proof documents exist.\n- Fixed: removed phantom `1-1-foo`, restored 4 stories to `done`, regenerated sprint-status.yaml. All 74 stories done.\n- **Root cause persists**: Ralph process (PID 74543, started 10:13AM) has been running all day. It reads sprint-state.json and writes back stale data that includes the phantom and reverted statuses. This has been happening since at least session 31.\n- **Needed fix**: Ralph must either (a) re-read state from disk before each write, or (b) clean up phantoms at startup, or (c) be restarted after the fix is deployed. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 prevents NEW phantoms but doesn't clean existing ones from ralph's in-memory state.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 3, Glob: 4\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known issue\n"}}
